sql:
SELECT access_type
FROM activity_access_logs
WHERE access_type = 'edit';

SELECT COUNT(*) AS access_count
FROM activity_access_logs
WHERE activity_id = 2;

SELECT resource_name
FROM shared_resources
WHERE category = 'security';

SELECT MAX(access_time) AS latest_access_time
FROM activity_access_logs
WHERE activity_id = 1;

SELECT user_id, MAX(access_time) AS most_recent_access_time
FROM activity_access_logs
WHERE user_id = 1;

external_knowledge:
Top 5 most active users refers to the users with the highest total counts of accessing various activities; 
Top 5 most frequently accessed activities are those with the highest counts of log entries in the activity_access_logs table; 
Latest version of an activity refers to the version with the highest version number for that activity.

sql:
SELECT MAX(version_number) AS latest_version
FROM activity_versions
WHERE activity_id = 1;

SELECT activity_id, MAX(version_number) AS latest_version
FROM activity_versions
GROUP BY activity_id;

SELECT MAX(version_number) AS highest_version
FROM activity_versions
WHERE activity_id = 2;
